[5] Cholera - India (Vadodara, Gujarat state)
Date: Tue 17 Jul 2018 12:39:39 IST
Source: The New Indian Express, Express News Service [edited]
https://indianexpress.com/article/cities/city-others/vadodara-village-declared-cholera-affected-5262417/


Vadodara district collector Shalini Agrawal on [Mon 16 Jul 2018] issued a notification declaring Khedkarmsiya village in Waghodia taluka [county] of Vadodara cholera-affected after 31 persons complained of symptoms of the disease.

According to chief district health officer Dr Uday Tilavat, 15 residents of Khedkarmsiya village had complained of diarrhea and vomiting on Sat 14 Jul 2018. Out of these, 6 were admitted to a community health centre in Jarod while 2 were referred to SSG hospital in Vadodara. Rest of the persons were treated locally and prescribed medicines. By Mon 16 Jul 2018, however, the number of affected persons increased to 31. Out of these, 21 have been admitted to hospitals.

"On [Sat 13 Jul 2018] we sent 6 samples for testing. 4 of the samples have tested positive and so we had to issue the notification," said Tilavat. He said that the reason for the spread of the waterborne disease was a damaged boring line, dumped with garbage, which had contaminated the water that was being pumped up to overhead tanks for drinking purposes. "We have done our preliminary task of cleaning and repairing the line," Tilavat added.

