[7] Cholera - China (Hong Kong) ex Malaysia
Date: Sun 15 Jul 2018
Source: Outbreak News Today [edited]
http://outbreaknewstoday.com/hong-kong-reports-imported-cholera-case-malaysia-63606/


Hong Kong health officials report investigating an imported cholera case in a 25 year old female patient who traveled to Malaysia. The patient traveled to Malaysia from 30 Jun 2018 to 3 Jul 2018 and developed diarrhea, abdominal pain, nausea, and vomiting started on 3 Jul 2018. She was admitted to Union Hospital on 8 Jul 2018 and was discharged 2 days later.

According to testing performed by the Centre for Health Protection's (CHP) Public Health Laboratory Services Branch, the patient's stool tested positive for toxigenic _Vibrio cholerae_ O1 serotype Ogawa. The patient was admitted to Princess Margaret Hospital on 11 Jul 2018 for isolation and management. She has been in a stable condition all along. Initial inquiries revealed that the patient had no travel companions in her recent trip and her home contacts remained asymptomatic. The CHP's investigations are ongoing.

"Most cholera patients have gastrointestinal symptoms such as diarrhea or vomiting. Some patients with severe symptoms present with a sudden onset of profuse diarrhea with rice-water-like and fishy smelling stools, nausea, and vomiting. Without prompt treatment, these patients may die from severe dehydration," a spokesman for the CHP said.

